      "content": "While I understand the side effects are bothersome, stopping early is still risky because the bacteria might not be fully eradicated. Nausea and tiredness are common, but it's best to discuss these side effects with your doctor. They can advise on whether a shorter course is safe or suggest remedies for the side effects while you finish the prescribed treatment.",
      "source": "target",
